title: Algerian U21 Cup
text:
The Algerian U21 Cup is an Algerian <a href="Association%20football">football</a> competition run by <a href="Algerian%20Football%20Federation">Algerian Football Federation</a> for under-21 sides. The competition was launched in 2011 and is open exclusively to clubs playing in the top two divisions of Algerian football.
<a href="JSM%20B%C3%A9ja%C3%AFa">JSM Béjaïa</a> won the inaugural edition of the competition by beating <a href="ASO%20Chlef">ASO Chlef</a> 2–0 in the 2012 final.
